HEADWORD: Complainer
<hw>Com*plain"er</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧m*pl⟦amac⟧n"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>One who complains or laments; one who finds fault; a
murmurer.</def> <rj><au>Beattie.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Speechless <qex>complainer</qex>, I will learn thy thought.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>complaining</ent>⟦br⟧
